'''''The Oxford Dictionary of English Etymology''''' is an [[etymological dictionary]] of the English language, published by [[Oxford University Press]]. The first editor of the dictionary was [[Charles Talbut Onions]] who spent his last twenty years largely devoted to completing ''The Oxford Dictionary of English Etymology'' (1966), which treated over 38,000 words and went to press just before his death.<ref>{{cite ODNB|first=J. A. W.|last=Bennett|authorlink=J. A. W. Bennett|id=35316|title=Onions, Charles Talbut (1873–1965)}}</ref> 

